A '''chief creative officer''' ('''CCO''') is the highest ranking position of the creative team within a company. Depending on the type of company, this position may be responsible for the overall look and feel of [[marketing]], [[Mass media|media]], and [[brand]]ing associated with the organization. The CCO may also be charged with managing, developing, and leading the team of [[creative director]]s, [[art director]]s, [[designer]]s, and [[copywriter]]s.
==Overall description== The CCO directs a company's creative output, developing the artistic design strategy that defines the company's brand.<ref name="do">Written By: Terry Masters, Edited By: Allegra J. Lingo [http://www.wisegeek.com/what-does-a-chief-creative-officer-do.htm "What Does a Chief Creative Officer Do"], 14 October 2014, Retrieved on 30 October 2014</ref> The CCO creates the unique image of the firm and deliver this distinctive design to consumers and to create a clear [[brand image]] which is a fundamental and essential work throughout the company. Advertisements present a certain memorable artistic design while also structured to accomplish functional goals. The CCO ensures that the design and functionality combine harmoniously so the firm can present a product that successfully represents its creative brand.<ref name="do" />
CCOs, in some cases are called [[creative directors]], are demanded in firms which involve creative thinking and artistic design. The position of generic head of marketing is usually replaced by chief creative officer in advertising firms.<ref name="do" /> The power of chief creative officer can even be compared to [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] and at the early stages of a small company, usually at the start of [[partnerships]], the CCO and the CEO manage jointly.<ref name="do" />
==Notable chief creative officers== *[[Riccardo Tisci]] of [[Burberry]]<ref>[https://www.burberryplc.com/en/news-and-media/press-releases/corporate/2018/burberry-appoints-riccardo-tisci-as-chief-creative-officer.html Burberry appoints Riccardo Tisci as Chief Creative Officer]. [[Burberry]]. 1 March 2018</ref> *[[Raf Simons]] of [[Calvin Klein]]<ref>[https://fashionista.com/2018/02/fashion-creative-directors-2018-guide Your Creative Director Cheat Sheet for the Fall 2018 Shows]. FASHIONISTA. 6 February 2018</ref> *[[Jennifer Lee (filmmaker)|Jennifer Lee]] of [[Walt Disney Animation Studios]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Walt Disney and Pixar Animation Studios Name Chief Creative Officers - The Walt Disney Company |url=https://www.thewaltdisneycompany.com/walt-disney-and-pixar-animation-studios-name-chief-creative-officers/ |website=The Walt Disney Company |date=19 June 2018}}</ref> *[[Pete Docter]] of [[Pixar]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Walt Disney and Pixar Animation Studios Name Chief Creative Officers - The Walt Disney Company |url=https://www.thewaltdisneycompany.com/walt-disney-and-pixar-animation-studios-name-chief-creative-officers/ |website=The Walt Disney Company |date=19 June 2018}}</ref> *[[Jessica Alba]] of [[The Honest Company]]<ref>[http://wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/beauty/jessica-alba-honest-beauty-launch-ulta-10342165/ "Jessica Alba’s Honest Beauty to Launch in Ulta"]</ref> *[[Scott Aukerman]] of [[Earwolf]] *[[Burnie Burns]] of [[Rooster Teeth Productions]]<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3ODSGbbWf7g "Burnie Burns"]</ref> *[[Nick Cannon]] of [[Radio Shack]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/nick-cannon-joins-radioshack-as-chief-creative-officer-300186936.html|title=Nick Cannon Joins RadioShack As Chief Creative Officer|website=PR Newswire|accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref> *[[Clive Davis]] of [[Sony Music Entertainment]]<ref>[http://www.zoominfo.com/p/Clive-Davis/17264028 "Mr. Clive Jay Davis"]</ref> *[[Bran Ferren]] of [[Applied Minds|Applied Minds LLC]], and [[Walt Disney Imagineering]] *[[John Gaburick]] of [[Impact Wrestling]] *[[Hugh Hefner]] of [[Playboy Enterprises]]<ref>[http://www.biography.com/people/hugh-hefner-9333521#synopsis "Hugh Hefner Biography"]</ref> *[[Geoff Johns]] of [[DC Entertainment]]<ref>[http://www.dcentertainment.com/management/geoff-johns "Geoff Johns"]</ref> *[[Jared Leto]] of [[Fandor (film site)|Fandor]] *[[Hisao Oguchi]] of [[Sega Sammy Holdings]] *[[Joe Quesada]] of [[Marvel Entertainment]] *[[Will.I.Am]] of [[3D Systems]] <ref>{{cite web|title=3D Systems Appoints will.i.am as Its Chief Creative Officer|url=http://www.3dsystems.com/press-releases/3d-systems-appoints-william-its-chief-creative-officer|website=3D Systems|accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref>
