'''''Mycoplasma haemomuris''''', formerly known as ''Haemobartonella muris''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Neimark|first=H|author2=Johansson, KE|author3=Rikihisa, Y|author4=Tully, JG|title=Revision of haemotrophic Mycoplasma species names|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|date=March 2002|volume=52|issue=Pt 2|pages=683|pmid=11931184|doi=10.1099/00207713-52-2-683 }}</ref> and ''Bartonella muris'', is a [[Gram stain|Gram-negative]] [[bacillus]].  It is known to cause [[anemia]] in rats and mice.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Marmorston-Gottesman|first=J|author2=Perla, D|title=The etiology of Bartonella muris anemia of the albino rat : the isolation of bartonella muris|journal=The Journal of Experimental Medicine|date=Oct 31, 1932|volume=56|issue=5|pages=763–75|pmid=19870100|pmc=2132187|doi=10.1084/jem.56.5.763}}</ref>

